      <div class="msgContentFrame"><b>Important notes to remember:</b> <br /> <br />-When doing Local Leve remember to finish all the materials even if you have completed or failed the Leve. Each leve has a set number of tries. <b>DO THEM ALL!</b> <br /> <br />-You can do the lower level crafts for skill. It wont be as much, but if you dont have/cant find the materials for the other stuff, feel free to keep going with lower level ones. <b>THEY WORK!</b> <br /> <br /><b>Guide: <br /> <br />Level 1 - 2</b> <br /> <br />Grab all your Rank 1 Local Leve's Do those first! <br />Method of completion: Standard <br />Tool: Main hand <br /> <br />Should be able to complete these with Standard, if you run into trouble, try doing rapids. <br /> <br /><b>Level 2 - 6</b> <br /> <br />Target: [Bone Harpoon Butt] x1 <br />Recipe: [Bone Chip] x 1 [wind shard] x2 <br />Method: Standard <br />Tool: Offhand <br />Notes: Can be done higher than 6 but you should save the rest of your bone chips for later at this point. <br /> <br /><b>Alternatives</b> <br />Target: [Copper fish hook] x12 <br />Recipe: [copper nugget] x1 [fire shard] x2 [Water Shard] x4 <br />Method: Standard <br />Tool: Mainhand <br /> <br />Target: [Fine sand] <br />Recipe: [sea sand] x6 [wind shard] x2 [lightning shard] x2 <br />Tool: Main <br />Method: Standard <br />Notes: Good for Alchemists.. If you have the sand, make it! <br /> <br /><b>Level 6 - 9</b> <br /> <br /><b>Start Armorer</b> <br /> <br />At this point, Its time to take up armorer and start making handfuls of copper rings, and do the beginning Leve's for Armorer. Purchase the wire from the vendor for 200g each. <br /> <br /> <br /><b>Level 1 - 6</b> <br /> <br />Target: [Handful of Copper Rings] <br />Recipe: [Copper wire] x1 [wind shard] x? [fire shard] x? <br />Method:Standard <br />Tool: Offhand <br /> <br /><b>End Armorer</b> <br /> <br /><b>Continue Goldsmithing</b> <br /> <br />Target:[Copper wristlet] <br />Recipe: [copper nugget] x1[handful of copper rings] x1 <br />Tool: Main <br />Method: Standard <br /> <br /><b>Alternative</b> <br /> <br />Target: [Copper Choker] <br />Recipe: [copper nugget] x1 [copper ingot] x1 [fire shard] x? [earth shard] x? <br />Tool: Main <br />Method: Standard <br /> <br /><b>Level 9 - 12~</b> <br /> <br />Heres where it starts getting hard. I Recommend you avoid Copper earrings/Copper rings until about level 12. Although you can complete them, they will be VERY difficult to do. <br /> <br /> <br />Target: [Bone ring] <br />Recipe: [bone chip]x1 <br />Method: rapid <br />Tool:mainhand <br /> <br /><b>Alternative</b> <br /> <br />Target: [fang earring] <br />Recipe: [copper nugget] x1 [bone chip] x1 <br />Method: rapid <br />Tool:mainhand <br /> <br />Target: [Copper earring] <br />Recipe: [copper nugget]x2 <br />Method: standard <br />Tool:mainhaind <br /> <br />Target: [Copper Ring] <br />Recipe: [copper nugget] x2 <br />Method: standard <br />Tool:mainhand <br /> <br /><b>Started getting 300+ skill at 11 with these, if you can do them do them!</b> <br /> <br />Target: [Raw Lapis Lazuli] x1 <br />Recipe: [Blue Quartz] x1 (obtained by Quarry) All colors obtained this way. <br />Method: rapid <br />Tool:offhand <br /> <br />Make them if you have the mats sitting around! <br />Can replace the &quot;Blue quartz&quot; with any color quartz as it makes its respective raw gem. <br /> <br />Target: [Lapis Lazuli] x1 <br />Recipe: [Raw Lapis Lazuli] x1 <br />Method: rapid <br />Tool:offhand <br /> <br />If you have the materials laying around, do make these and save them! <br />Can replace the &quot;Raw Lapis Lazuli&quot; with any color raw gem as it makes its respective gem. <br /> <br /><b>Additional notes:</b> <br /> <br />Tried a few things here for a friend. These are worth it if people need them. Quite a significant upgrade for a Thaumaturge. <br /> <br />Target: [Marbled Eye] <br />Recipe: [Wind Rock] x1 OR [Water Rock] x1 [Wind Crystal] x1 [Water Shard] x2 <br />Method: Rapid <br />Tool: offhand <br /> <br />Made this at level 12 with a slight degree of difficulty (66% success rate) <b>DO AT OWN RISK</b> <br /> <br />Target: [Copper Scepter] <br />Recipe: [Marbled Eye] x1 [Copper Ingot] x1 [Animal Glue] x1 <br />Method: Rapid <br />Tool: offhand <br /> <br />Made at level 12 with a minor degree of difficulty (80% Success rate) <br /> <br />Target: [Decorated Copper Scepter] <br />Recipe: [Copper Scepter] x1 [Brass Nugget] x1 [Bronze Nugget] x1 <br />Method: Rapid <br />Tool: offhand <br /> <br />Also made this with the materials left over and the extra copper scepters at level 12 with a decent success rate. (no stats as to how well yet) DO AT OWN RISK <br /> <br /><b>----Closing----</b> <br />This was written in Open beta, powerleveled from a vendor the whole way. <br />Subject to change. <br /> <br />When Retail hits, i will continue this guide, as i level goldsmithing. Stay tuned! <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 21st 2010 11:30am by bigbyte </span></i></div>
